.
 A function is of class 
\begin_inset Formula ${\tt C}^{k}$
\end_inset

 if it has 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 continuous derivatives.
 The Lebesgue measure on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 is denoted by 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

.
 Given some sets 
