, a set-valued map 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

 from 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 to subsets of 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 is denoted by 
\begin_inset Formula $F:A\rightrightarrows B$
\end_inset

.
 The notation 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{\mathrm{co}}A$
\end_inset

 denotes the closed convex hull of the set 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

.
 The notation 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{B}_{\delta}\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

, for 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta>0$
\end_inset

, is used to denote the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ y\in\mathbb{R}^{n}:\left\Vert x-y\right\Vert <\delta\right\} $
\end_inset

.
 The interior of a set 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

, denoted by 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{int}\left(S\right)$
\end_inset

, is the set of all points 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in S$
