\end_inset

.
 A function 
\begin_inset Formula $y:\mathcal{I}_{y}\to\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 is called a Filippov solution of 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{y}=h\left(y,t\right)$
\end_inset

 on the interval 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{I}_{y}\subseteq\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}$
\end_inset

, if 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 is absolutely continuous on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{I}_{y}$
