, and is a solution to the differential inclusion 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{y}\stackrel{{\rm a.e.}}{\in}K\left[h\right]\left(y,t\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Clarke's generalized gradient for a locally Lipschitz function 
\begin_inset Formula $V:\mathbb{R}^{n}\times\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}\to\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 is defined as 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial V\left(x,t\right)\triangleq\overline{\text{co}}\left\{ \lim\nabla V\left(x,t\right):\left(x_{i},t_{i}\right)\to\left(x,t\right),\left(x_{i},t_{i}\right)\not\in\Omega_{V}\right\} $
\end_inset

, where 
