-norm, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\Vert \dot{\eta}+k_{1}\eta\right\Vert _{1}=\left(\dot{\eta}+k_{1}\eta\right)^{\top}K\left[\text{sgn}\right]\left(\dot{\eta}+k_{1}\eta\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Using the definitions of the chain rule and the 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{1}$
\end_inset

-norm, taking the time-derivative of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq: P function"

\end_inset

, using Leibniz's rule, and substituting 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq: Filtered Tracking Error Ensemble."

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq: Auxiliary Tracking Error ensemble"

\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq: P function"

\end_inset

 into the resulting expression yields that 
\begin_inset Formula $t\mapsto P\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

 satisfies the differential inclusion
